inski,Profiles.Des,Cookbook.ExcelPaste,Profiles.Flox,PmWiki.Security,PmWiki.Notify,PmWiki.PmWiki,Profiles.TeganDowling,Cookbook.WikiCalendar,PmWiki.CookbookExpireDiff,Cookbook.UploadGroups,PmWiki.AuthorTracking,PmWiki.UploadVariables,Cookbook.RenamePage,PmWiki.UrlApprovals,Cookbook.LimitWikiGroups,Profiles.Mike,Cookbook.IncludeFieldPage,Site.AuthUser,PmWiki.HierarchicalGroups,Skins.Gemini,Skins.FixFlow,Skins.Triad,Cookbook.AuthUser,Cookbook.UserAuth,PmWiki.Upgrades,Cookbook.ExpireDiff,Localization.XLPageTemplate,PmWikiDa.XLPage,PmWiki.GroupCustomizations,PmWiki.Tablename,Profiles.StirlingWestrup,Profiles.HansB,PmWiki.Tdoo,PmWiki.DeletingPages,Cookbook.PagelistTemplateSamples,Cookbook.ImportText,PmWiki.FunctionList,Profiles.Caveman,PmWiki.WikiTrails,Cookbook.WikiTrails,Cookbook.DynamicTrails,Cookbook.DynamicWikiTrails,Cookbook.QuickPageTableOfContents,Cookbook.PageTableOfContents,Cookbook.EditTemplates,Profiles.Chris,PITS.00500,PITS.00378,Profiles.Diafygi,Cookbook.ShowHide,Cookbook.NewPageBoxPlus,PmWiki.Images,Localization.StateOfTranslationTemplate,PmWikiPl.StateOfTranslation,Profiles.JerzyTarasiuk,PmWikiPl.PmWikiPl,Profiles.SamWilson,Cookbook.UploadForm,Cookbook.ThumbList,Profiles.Simon,PmWiki.Internationalizations,Profiles.Andreas,Cookbook.DragDropMultiUpload,Skins.PmWiki-responsive,Cookbook.RelativeURLs,Cookbook.RelativeURLs-Users,PmWiki.Support,Profiles.Gnuzoo,PmWiki.Chat,Cookbook.RedirectSilent,PITS.01446
text=(:Summary: Ask your questions about PmWiki here, after checking the [[documentation index]] and [[FAQ]]:)%0a%0aThis is a page where you can ask questions about PmWiki.%0aYou will need to count on someone coming along and answering your question, so please be patient.%0a%0aA quicker, more effective way to ask a question is to join the pmwiki-users [[mailing list(s)]] and '''''send your question to the list.'''''%0aUnfortunately answers to the list do not always get posted here, perhaps you can help keep PmWiki up to date by making sure your answer is added here or elsewhere in the documentation.%0a%0aSee also [[How to get assistance]].%0aIn particular please try to [[PmWiki/HowToGetAssistance#reproduce | reproduce]] the issue in a [[Test/]] page.%0a>>faq%3c%3c%0a%0aQ: Is this the right place to post my question?%0a%0aA: It might be.  Posting to the [[mailing list(s)]] would work better, but adding it here may get you an answer. Make sure your question doesn't appear on the [[FAQ | PmWiki FAQ]] page first. You might also try [[Site/search]]ing pmwiki.org to find an answer.%0a%0aA: %25note%25 If your question is about a specific [[Documentation(Index)]] page or [[Cookbook/]]/[[Skins/]] recipe please ask it on the recipe-Talk page (if it doesn't exist, just create it).%0a%0a(:searchbox:)%0a%0aIf you still can't find what you need to know and you don't want to use the pmwiki-users [[mailing list(s)]], then post your question on this page.%0a%0aOnce your question has been answered, it may be moved to the [[FAQ Candidate]] page or even the [[FAQ | PmWiki FAQ]] page, so if it disappears look for it on those two pages.%0a----%0a''Looks like I'm the first one adding to this in nearly a year! ''%0a%0aQ: I'm trying to decide whether to set up a new instance of PmWiki on a self-hosted NAS, or to migrate an existing instance.%0aWhat's stopping me from just migrating the older one are things like changes in IP address.%0aWhen I look at a page from the old instance, I see something like this:%0a%0a--> version=pmwiki-2.2.130 ordered=1 urlencoded=1%0a--> agent=Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1; Win64; x64; rv:56.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/56.0 Waterfox/56.3%0a--> author=%0a--> charset=UTF-8%0a--> csum=%0a--> ctime=1596706067%0a--> host=2.26.58.171%0a%0aThis last line, the host IP, is the previous IP, not the one for my NAS.%0aSo I worry that simply copying the installation folder from one server to another won't work, if all the pages refer to some other IP address. %0aThe documentation about [[PmWiki.BackupAndRestore]] is a bit sparse in this regard. It seems that it's referring to restoration onto the same server. %0aSo, I can simplify my question: can an instance be copied across from one server to another, provided the folder structure remains intact? [[~dp]] October 05, 2020, at 11:59 PM%0a%0aA: %25Py%25 The "host" page attribute is the IP address of the last editor, not of the server, see [[PageFileFormat]]. It is not used to make links, stored for reference, for example to be able to block a user or review the raw server logs for activity from that person. To answer your question, yes, mostly. Move your entire installation (pmwiki.php, scripts, cookbook, local, wikilib.d, wiki.d, uploads), and review local/config.php and other scripts you may have modified in the local and cookbook directories to see if some local configuration in that file refers to the old IP address or the old server name, you may need to update it, notably $ScriptUrl, $FarmPubDirUrl, $PubDirUrl. --[[~Petko]] October 06, 2020, at 06:20 AM%0a%0a----%0aQ: I manually purged hundreds of spam files from the wiki.d directory.  Is there a way to have AllRecentChanges regenerate itself so it no longer shows these purged files but continues to show all the others?  (I'd like to see just real changes made by our group on this page and not what has been purged.)%0a%0aA: Try Cookbook:RebuildRC. --[[~Petko]] November 25, 2019, at 02:27 PM%0a%0aThanks!!  This worked great when I used it with this string:%0a%0a$RebuildRCPattern = '*.*,-PmWiki*.*,-Site*.*,-Category.*,-*.RecentChanges,-*.AllRecentChanges';%0a%0a%0a----%0aQ: How to set a custom bookmarklet favicon (not the default website favicon) in Firefox?%0a%0aA: I'm not sure there is a way to change the icon of a specific bookmark different from the icon for the domain. [[https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/favicon-customizer/|This]] or [[https://youtu.be/7u2jBitDcho|this]] may work, or not. This is something not specifically related to PmWiki though -- maybe ask at some forum(s) dedicated to Firefox? --[[~Petko]] May 22, 2019, at 10:39 AM%0a----%0aQ: How to put large preformatted text into a scroll-able area.%0a%0aComing from wikimedia (and as such a PmWiki noob) i'm probably going the wrong way about this but it is totally unclear to me how one manage to put some (pre-formatted) text into a box. fwiw,  i've read the documentation many times and the closest i seem to be able to get is something like this:%0a[@%0a>>frame indent color=green bgcolor=blue font-family=monospace height=auto max-height=200px width=550px overflow=scroll padding-botttom=10px border=3px%3c%3c%0ahundreds of lines of pre formatted text that contains long lines (about 200-500 characters width) and can not be wrapped.%0a>>%3c%3c%0a@]%0a%0aNo matter what i try, the overflow attributes keeps being removed, which results in display havoc :-)%0a[[~SomeNoob]] May 15, 2019, at 06:29 AM%0a%0aA: %25Py%25 Overflow is indeed not supported out of the box, but you can add it with such a line in config.php: @@$WikiStyleCSS[] = 'overflow';@@ then it should work. Alternatively, or in addition, especially if you reuse these styles you can [[LocalCustomizations|create a file pub/css/local.css]] and place there any custom styles for a "class" like @@.monoscroll { font-family: monospace; overflow:scroll; [other styles] } @@ then in the wiki code just use the classname like [@>>frame indent monoscroll%3c%3c@]. Or, if you include the "frame" and "indent" styles into the @@.monoscroll@@ class, simply [@>>monoscroll%3c%3c@]. If PmWiki doesn't recognize a keyword as a [[WikiStyle(s)]], it considers it a CSS classname. --[[~Petko]] May 15, 2019, at 07:21 AM%0a%0a-> Thank you very much for the quick reply @Petko. Works like a charm and thereby you've included 3 additional answers on (followup) questions that i (still) had. Saves me from asking those separately :-) [[~SomeNoob]] May 15, 2019, at 08:23 AM%0a----%0aQ: How can I make a reaction to wrong password input? I have the readonly site with [@?action=login@] link on every it's page. If user types the wrong password (''wrong'' could mean that there is not such password in config.php OR that user access level was not changed after login attempt), I want to show him a message about it. Is it possible in any way? The problem is that after user loggin in PmWiki makes redirect to [@$pagename@] with no params. [[~Finar]] April 22, 2019, at 05:20 PM%0a%0aA: %25Py%25 There is no wrong password for PmWiki, just wrong password for a particular action at a particular page. When a user types any password, PmWiki remembers it. If the user tries to access a protected page or action, PmWiki tries all passwords the user knows (typed within the current session), and if one of these is sufficient for the page and action, the user is permitted to access, otherwise the authentication form is shown. Instead of ?action=login you can use ?action=edit. Alternatively see [[Conditional markup]] for either [@(:if authid:)@] or [@(:if auth edit:)@] which you could place in a sidebar, topbar or in Site.PageActions. That way users can see a change in the interface after the ?action=login form. --[[~Petko]] May 08, 2019, at 08:59 AM%0a%0aA:%25Py%25 Or, you can try this in config.php: @@ $HandleAuth['login'] = 'edit'; @@ --[[~Petko]] May 09, 2019, at 06:27 AM%0a%0a----%0aQ: Is it safe to name a group and/or a page with a single letter (e.g. A/A, A/B, etc.)? [-([[~Frank]] April 30, 2018, at 10:55 PM)-]%0a%0a%25Py%25 Yes: A.A, A.B, A.2 are all fine. Note that in the default installation a WikiGroup name cannot start with, or be a single digit like in 1.1, this is controlled by the variable $GroupPattern. --[[~Petko]] May 01, 2018, at 01:15 AM%0a%0aThanks. [-([[~Frank]] May 01, 2018, at 01:33 AM)-]%0a----%0aQ: I've set $ScriptUrl and $PubDirUrl to http://example.com, but PmWiki redirects to http://www.example.com. I can't find this redirect anywhere in the config, .htaccess file or in pmwiki.php. Where do I disable this obnoxious behaviour?%0a%0a%25Py%25 Try a simple HTML file like http://example.com/test.html. If it still redirects to the "www." subdomain, it has nothing to do with PmWiki, this is either a DNS redirect (sometimes a TXT record) or an Apache configuration (in httpd.conf or another config file). Check the documentation at your hosting and DNS provider(s). --[[~Petko]] April 12, 2018, at 09:38 AM%0a%0aThanks, it turns out somebody messed with the domain config, yeah. I was pulling my hair out because I know the apache config is correct (and I can't access the domain control panel). Thanks!%0a----%0aQ: In older versions of pmwiki (e.g. 2.2.91) it was no problem, to create a page with name starting with small letter (e.g. [@ [[Main/test]] @]. If I do this now in newer version (2.2.102) it does not work. The system trys to create a page like this: cb_toupperbcb_toupperoupperest. How can I get it work? Thanks for your help. Astrid, October 19, 2017%0a%0a%25Py%25 Make sure you have updated all files, especially pmwiki.php and the files in the scripts directory. Also, and this is very important, you must not rename pmwiki.php to index.php, index.php needs to contain simply [@%3c?php include_once("pmwiki.php");@] otherwise you may forget to update it and may run an older, incompatible, or vulnerable version. --[[~Petko]] October 19, 2017, at 03:55 AM%0a%0aThanx. The pmwiki, where the error appears, I installed fresh from downloading the tgz and putting the german language on it. I did not rename the pmwiki.php, I did it with the include.%0a%0a%25Py%25 It does work here: [[Main/test]] (PHP 5.2) and also on my home server (PHP 7.1) so I assume there is something different in your installation. 2.2.102 doesn't have a cb_toupper reference, so either you run 2.2.103-104, or on 102 you have some newer local customization that requires 103 or later. Does the German installation include custom $MakePageNamePatterns variables? --[[~Petko]] October 19, 2017, at 08:45 AM%0a%0aThanx. [[Main/test]] is working for me. I updated to 104 with German. Now it is working with pagenames beginning with small letters for me too. Thanx. :)%0a%0a----%0aQ: I am getting this error when attempting to edit any page: http://carp-mi.net/?pagename=CARP.HomePage?action=edit%0a----%0aA: You are using a very old PmWiki version that is no longer supported, and will likely raise problems with recent PHP versions. Try installing the latest PmWiki version in another directory, then copy the files from the old wiki.d directory into the new one. Your skin may also require an update. If you require assistance [[Mailing lists|get in touch]]. --[[~Petko]] January 19, 2017, at 04:14 PM%0a----%0aQ: I'm very happy with PmWiki's syntax. But with hundreds of pages sometimes it's hard to find out the correct name of a page I'd like to set a link to. Is there a possibility to create something like a popup where I can select an internal page from a list instead of typing the link? DokuWiki for example has this built-in. I could create something with Fox, but perhaps there is an easier way. Thanks for help. Daniel, October 3, 2016%0aA: You can do it yourself. I will describe one possible way (I used in my project):%0a* edit [[Site.EditForm]] adding some [[PmWiki/PageLists|pagelist]] which will generate the list of links you want to be on hand. Actually this is 80%25 of the goal, if you are happy with ctrl+c/ctrl+v, you can stop here. If you want get more pretty result, then continue;%0a* use some CSS code for styling this list;%0a* use some jQuery solution to make this list of links clickable.%0a[[~Finar]] August 14, 2018, at 03:44 PM%0a----%0aQ: After copying one complete wiki from one server to another the wiki works great with one exception: GroupHeaders and Footers are not shown anymore. There are only two things that changed at the new server: It is a Unix server (Windows before) and the authentication runs via LDAP. I tried almost everything: Setting new access rights, creating new groups and pages, but PMWiki won't show any header or footer. What reasons could there be? August 31, 2016%0a%0aA:  Hi, now I resolved the problem. It was about lower/upper case letters, which is important to unix, but not to windows. All my header an footer files were named "Groupheader" and "Groupfooter", while the pmwiki.php needs "GroupHeader" and "GroupFooter". So it was very easy to fix!%0a%0a----%0aQ: How do I create a link to firefox "about:addons" ? Augst 9, 2016%0a%0aA: You can add an intermap prefix, see [[InterMap]], however most browsers will not follow such links: about:addons. %0a%0a----%0aQ: I have been waiting for developers to update their cookbook recipes for the preg_replace() /e change. Some have updated the code while many have not. Queries on Talk pages have not gotten results. I took the plunge and started modifying the routines myself. Some are working OK while others are not. Is there someone who could check my work and fix it or tell me how to fix it?%0aHere are the recipe files I changed: markupexprplus.php, extendcond.php, guibuttons.php, httpvariables.php, rename.php%0a%0a-- [[~DannyB]] November 6, 2014%0a%0a----%0aQ: I Need to Change the way, the form-Buttons work (Save, Save and edit, Preview, Cancel). I allready deleted the preview button, because I don't Need it. For the save and cancel button: They should perform as they do but instead of linking to the edited site, they should link to a defined site (on this one, I want to write something like this: "Your Input has been saved" - so no linking to the edited site). Please help.%0a%0aA: Found the answer myself on http://www.pmwiki.org/wiki/PmWiki/EditVariables !%0a%0a----%0aQ: I just installed pmwiki through GoDaddy. When I try to save an edit, or enter a password to get into the administration site, instead of taking me to the appropriate webpage, I get a message that says that the server sent no data. It also says, "Error code: ERR_EMPTY_RESPONSE" Does anyone know why this would happen? This happens every time I try to save an edit or enter a password. "I have the same issue...is there anyone who can explain this - DR"%0a%0aA: Recent PmWiki versions (2.2.56 and newer) should work fine on GoDaddy hosting plans. If the problem appears only when a Cookbook recipe is enabled, we may be able to help updating the recipe too.%0a%0a----%0aQ: I'd like to define links within Site/InterMap using a dynamic method based on what pages currently exist in two groups.  I was intending to use a custom page list template (and still would like to) however, entries only seem to count if they're entered manually.  I'd hate to have to manually copy and paste the results for the links to update.  How can I automate this?%0a%0aA: Perhaps you can define PmWiki:InterMap links in your configuration file instead of on the InterMap page. Also, although it's not dynamic, you can partially automate any copy and paste chore by generating the markup you want to paste using a custom pagelist. Use [%25%25@ and @%25%25] tactfully to ensure that the output is markup.%0a----%0a%0aQ: Is there a way to integrate Matomo (formerly Piwik) - web analytics to PmWiki sites? (https://matomo.org/)%0a%0aA: You can put the JavaScript code (and the noscript image URL) in $HTMLFooterFmt['matomo']%0a----%0aQ: Is there a way to link to a local pdf document such that the link in PmWiki opens it in the browser?%0a%0aI am using OSX Safari.  If I type a link [@file:///Users/.../file.pdf@] into Safari, it will open the file.  If however I add that link to a Wiki page (web-based, but accessed through Safari on the same machine), it will not.  Is there a way?  Many thanks, [[Profiles/Conrad]], 23 August 2012%0a----%0aQ: Is it possible to have blocklists by group?%0a%0aI want to block URLs on Talk pages which are world editable, but allow them in Main pages which are editable only by @contributors. It seems intuitive that Talk.Blocklist should be the blocklist for the Talk group, but (as the documentation does say) all blocklist pages are used. I tried this conditional in Talk.Blocklist%0a%0a[@%0a(:if equal "{*$Group}" "Talk" :)%0ablock:/[^\w\\]href\b/%0a(:ifend:)%0a@]%0a%0abut this continued to block all URLs in all groups.%0a%0a>>Py%3c%3c%0aYou can reset the $BlocklistPages for the Talk group. In the file plwiki/local/Talk.php, add such a line: [@%0a  $BlocklistPages = array('SiteAdmin.Blocklist', 'Talk.Blocklist');%0a@]%0aYou may also want to enable Blocklist only for the Talk group, in that case, set the line @@ $EnableBlocklist = 1; @@ in Talk.php, and remove it from config.php. If the Talk.php file doesn't exist, create it with a first line containing [@%3c?php@] then the other lines below, see [[LocalCustomizations]]. --[[~Petko]] April 15, 2012, at 10:33 AM%0a>>%3c%3c%0a----%0aQ: I am trying to create a link to a different port on the same machine as the wiki, where I have a different service running (like: [=http://name.tld:8000/=]); with a ":" and port number before the trailing "/".  The best I can get with Intermap is ([=http://name.tld/:8000.=]), or ([=http://name.tld..:8000/=]), neither of which work, of course, and a static link is out of the question. Any ideas?%0amaxnort-12-23-11%0a%0a%25Py%25 You can enter in your page [@[[Site.InterMap]]@] the address with the port number. The following works on my wiki. --[[~Petko]] December 24, 2011, at 03:24 AM%0a[@%0a  MyLink     http://www.example.net:8080/%0a@]%0a----%0aQ: In guiedit.php line 71, I removed "style='border:0'" and added "class='guieditbutton'". I defined this style class in my skin class file. It's work well but I'm searching for a way to do that without modify the PMWiki Core. Is someone have a hint for me? Thanks! [[~CarolineGuénette]]%0a%0aA: Le plus simple serait de copier ce fichier du dossier pmwiki/scripts au%0adossier pmwiki/cookbook. Puis, dans local/config.php, ajouter:%0a%0a  if ($action=='edit') include_once("$FarmD/cookbook/mon-guiedit.php");%0a%0a(et supprimer ou commenter la ligne $EnableGUIButtons = 1;)%0a(email answer from [[Profiles/Petko]]. merci!)%0a%0a----%0aPosted by Nakul on November 11, 2011%0a%0aQ: I have used mod_rewrite to enable cleaner URLS, so that now when I type "musicmind.biz/John Coltrane" in my address bar, it takes me to http://musicmind.biz/JohnColtrane/JohnColtrane". For the sake of good organization, I would like every single page to be a category page, so that it may be well cross-indexed. Therefore, I would like it if the user was defaulted to the category group whenever entering a "musicmind.biz/namespace" such that musicmind.biz/page would arrive at--> musicmind.biz/category/page. If this is not possible, I would like to shorten the "Category" group into something more accessible to users, like "1," or "w." I have perused the FAQ and did see this explanation: "An administrator can override the default category group name of "Category" by setting the $CategoryGroup variable in config.php to another group name." However, that's all the information I have found and have not been able to successfully implement the name change. Going along the lines of data organization, can pages be longer than 2 namespaces? Ex. musicmind.biz/Category/John Coltrane - A Love Supreme - Acknowledgement/Intro Saxophone Riff Help is greatly appreciated, as I cannot deposit data onto the server until the fundamental naming scheme is resolved.%0a%0a----%0a%0aQ: My favourite statistic tool needs to have a %3c?php include_once('whateverpath/statinclude.php'); ?> statement include into the pmwiki code.  Which is the best place to put it into? Posted by Arno on November 8 2011%0a%0a%25Py%25 See [[http://www.pmichaud.com/pipermail/pmwiki-users/2011-November/059617.html|this post on the mailing list]]. --[[~Petko]] December 24, 2011, at 03:30 AM%0a%0a----%0aPosted by GaryW on July 21 2011%0a%0aQ: Is it possible to create buttons or links for invoking the various page actions instead of manually typing them in the URL?%0a%0aA: You can append to any URL "?action=". For example:%0a%0a(:markup:)%0a[[{$FullName}?action=source|View this page's source markup.]]%0a(:markupend:)%0a%0aA: You can edit your page Site.PageActions and add such action links there. Then, the links will appear in the actions bar on all pages.%0a%0a----%0aPosted by Ericp June 7th, 2011%0a%0aQ: Is it possible to have a bilingual site?%0a%0aTo be more precise, I want each page to have 2 different copies, one for language A and B. If the user currently see a language A page, clicking on other pages will only show A page. Then the uses can click a special link to switch his language to B. Then all pages clicked will show the B version of the page.%0a%0aCan it be done? \\%0aIs there a cookbook to do the job?\\%0aElse, is there another way to have a bilingual site?\\%0a%0aThank You%0a%0aA: Yes, it is possible.%0a%0aSee [[Cookbook/MultiLanguage]] and [[Cookbook/MultiLanguageViews]] for 2 different approaches.%0a%0aNote also the XL capabilities%0a%0a----%0aQ: i'd like to add figure markup(html5).. but i couldn't find the way... can you help me? [@%0ainput)%0a%0a(:fig $arg:) // $arg like class or id or style="attr:value;"%0a imgpattern or [[imglink|img]]%0a caption (with some inline markup)%0a(:figend:)%0a%0aoutput1)%0a[@%0a%3cfigure> // this is block element.%0a      %3cimg ~~> or %3ca href="">%3cimg ~~>%3c/a>%0a      %3cfigcaption>%0a            blahblah (with some inline markup)%0a      %3c/figcaption>%0a%3c/figure>%0a@]%0aoutput2)%0a[@%0a%3cfigure> // this is block element.%0a      %3cimg ~~> or %3ca href="">%3cimg ~~>%3c/a>%0a      %3cimg ~~> or %3ca href="">%3cimg ~~>%3c/a>%0a      %3cimg ~~> or %3ca href="">%3cimg ~~>%3c/a>%0a      %3cfigcaption>%0a            blahblah (with some inline markup)%0a      %3c/figcaption>%0a%3c/figure>%0a%0a @] [[~she]] March 02, 2011, at 07:35 AM%0a%0aQ: Would you have a idea about using [@natsort($array);@] into the function to make Page List?  it's not good when numberic list displays.%0aA: You could use [@$PageListSortCmp['natsort'] = 'strnatcasecmp($x, $y)';@]\\%0aSee also [[PmWiki/CustomPagelistSortOrder]] and [[Cookbook/CustomPagelistSortOrderFunctions]]. --[[~Petko]] February 01, 2011, at 02:07 AM%0a%0aoh! thank you!! i'll try~! ;) --[[~she]]%0a%0a----%0aQ: Is it possible to make the "text" part of  [=(:title text:)=] be an image reference?%0aI'd like to have a particular font (which isn't a "usual" font) for my titles, and I figured the best way to do that would be to create title images.  Thanks%0a%0a----%0aQ: I have some problems with Pagelists and Conditions%0aI installed the Cookbook [[Cookbook.MovePage]]. As soon a page ist moved from the Group e.g. "Shows" to "Showsarchive" it still exists in the group "Shows". Therefore I want to give out all the "Shows.*" pages in a pagelists but not showing the pages that are already in the group "Showsarchive.*".%0a%0aIt should be a conditions something like this:%0a%0a(:markup:)%0a(:pagelist group="Shows" fmt="#simple" if="!group Showsarchive.*" :)%0a(:markupend:)%0a%0aBut i have not clue and invested already hours in finding out. Maybe you can help me? That would save my day!%0a[[~Jean Baptiste]] On May 24, 2010 - at 13:28 PM%0a%0aA: I just found out, Yeah:%0a(:markup:)%0a(:pagelist group="Shows" fmt="#simple" if="!exists Showsarchive.{=$Name}" :)%0a(:markupend:)%0a[[~Jean Baptiste]] On May 26, 2010 - at 1:13 AM%0a%0a----%0aQ: I have some code that is part of the HTML of my page. It is encapsulated in a DIV and has style information. These divs control the location and style of the [@ :trail: @] and [@ :audience: @] information. Since there is no Div Id, I can't assign -my own- style to this. I have dug EVERYWHERE in the files and not found where this is defined. I have even used the command in the config file to shut off all the styles from the script files. Yet the formatting of the light blue and light yellow boxes remains.%0a%0a%0a----%0aQ: How can I link files to intranet (local) files?%0aI have followed the recipe described "including the prefix [@'file:///'@] (for Internet Explorer at least) and [@file:///S:\ProjPlan.mpp@] and [@[[Shared S drive->file:///S:\]]@] on a Windows file system" but it didn't work. I have also followed the procedure linking to [@"(eg \\server1\rootdirectory\subdirectory)"@] without any success at all. The path to Windows Explorer inside the PmWiki pages are prompting the page "file not included on this server". I would like to open the file on the source folder and not on the browser. Can somebody give me a hint?%0a[[~Burialmound]] On September 10, 2009 - at 17:12 PM%0a%0a%25Py%25 The recipe Cookbook:DirList provides a workaround. --[[~Petko]] January 18, 2011, at 02:13 PM%0a%0a----%0aQ: How can I have a SideBar the will be presented to every existing group?%0aI have installed PmWiki and the corresponding Brazilian Portuguese translated pages. When I click the PmWiki icon on the top left, I am redirected to the Main page. There is no problem about that! However, when  I click the Search button on the top right or on the bottom of the page, I am redirected to the Search page corresponding to the Brazilian translation, which has a different SideBar from the one where I built all our pages. I mean, all our pages were created based on the main Site/SideBar and not on the PmWikiPtBr. I have tried to redirect the Brazilian Portuguese Search engine to the Main page and was lucky, (but I fear I did something not the way it should be). What I did exactly was: I changed lines 28 and 55 that have the codes\\\%0a[@%3ca href='{$ScriptUrl}/$[{$SiteGroup}/Search]'>$[Search]%3c/a>%3c/div>@]\\\%0ato\\\%0a[@%3ca href='http://192.../pmwiki/pmwiki.php?n=Site.Search'>$[Search]%3c/a>%3c/div> %3cdiv id='wikifoot'>@]\\\%0aon the pmwiki.tmpl. I did that because I don't want to have two different SideBars on our Wiki but still want to have the translation to the buttons (recent changes, search, view, edit etc). I am desperate, my friends and hope you can help me.%0a[[~Burialmound]] August 19, 2009%0a%0a%25Py%25 Remove your page [@[[PmWikiPtBr.SideBar]]@] and possibly the file @@pmwiki/wikilib.d/PmWikiPtBr.SideBar@@ to get rid of the existing sidebar. Another way to do is to edit [@[[PmWikiPtBr.SideBar]]@] and to replace all of its content with [@(:include Site.SideBar:)@] . --[[~Petko]] August 19, 2009, at 04:19 PM%0a%0aPetko, thanks for your help. I erased the content of [@[[PmWikiPtBr.SideBar]]@] and included the line [@(:include Site.SideBar:)@] and it worked.%0aP.S. I undid all the previous changes described by me above (and Petko's suggestion still worked).%0a[[~Burialmound]] On August 20, 2009 - at 11:52 AM%0a%0a----%0aQ: How can I deny the access of non authorized users to the index of ''my''wiki/uploads page?%0aThank You, [[~Tomita]] July 18, 2009%0aA: Please see information and faqs on the [[uploads]] and [[uploads admin]] pages.%0a----%0aQ: I want a simple events display. For this matter I added a pagetext variable "EventsDate:2009-04-12" and for grouping the events a variable "EventsGroup:200904"%0a%0aFor the pagelist I created something like this, but sadly it doesn't work. If there are two ore more events in one month, then the heading (in template first) ist repeated for every event. Why?%0a%0a[@%0a[[#EventsList]]%0a(:template first {{=$FullName}$:EventsGroup})}:)%0a!! {(ftime "%25m / %25Y" {{=$FullName}$:EventsDate})}%0a(:template each:)%0a* [[{=$FullName}|{(ftime %25d.%25m.%25Y {{=$FullName}$:EventsDate})} {=$Titlespaced}]]%0a[[#EventsListend]]%0a@]%0a----%0aQ: Is there a way to change the background colour on the total page?  Not just a block but all background?  I am familiar with Triad but the colours are wrong and that also introduces more problems.%0a%0aPosted 2/6/09%0a%0aA: %25Py%25Yes, [= >pub >skins >your Skin (example: pmwiki) >.css >body { background-color: #xxxxxx; } =]%0a2/26/09 [[~Hirsch]]%0a%0a----%0aQ: Is there a searching equivalent of Ctrl+F (Find) in PMWiki? I have an internal page (sorry, no link to provide) that contains a table/catalog of about 1,000 entries that I would like my audience to be able to search thru using a searchbox to enter a keyword and skip down the page thru the instances of that word, rather than using Ctrl+F. It needs to be confined to searching on that page only. So far, i can only find searching options that return a list of pages that include the search word. Is there an option that mimics the "find" functionality of Ctrl+F?%0a%0aposted 1/29/09%0a%0a----%0a%0a%0aQ: [[http://www.pmwiki.org/wiki/PmWiki/Images|Images]] - page describes as a picture-frame with [-[=%25rframe%25=]-] or [-[=%25lframe%25=]-] is generated.%0a%0aQ: Where I can modify the PmWiki-predefined formula [-[=%25rframe%25=]-]?%0a%0aThank you very much%0a%0a-> Norbert Hirsch%0a-%3c 081219%0a%0aA: %25Py%25 Set in config.php this line : \\%0a@@$WikiStyle['rframe'] = array('class' => 'myframeclass');@@\\%0aSee [[PmWiki/WikiStyles]] for more information.%0a%0aThank you, [[~Hirsch]]%0a%0a----%0aQ:Is there a way to convert my entire website to html based documentation tools like Microsoft HTML Help ?%0a%0a----%0aQ:how can i hide the standalone server window so that it runs in the background without getting diplayed?%0a->Pranab  13.11.08%0a%0a%0a%0a----%0aQ: Do special characters in links require prepratory configuration?%0a%0aIs PmWiki "out of the box" supposed to support special characters in links? I have some problems with umlauts after moving the server, and umlaut links don't work either in my own wiki or in a fresh install with everything at the default settings. I tought after the implementation of [[PITS.00053]] umlauts worked in links, but I'm not sure if they require some additional configuration, and can't find anything in the documentation about it.%0a%0aInstead of well-encoded links like this: [[Test/PageNäme]], I get: "Main/PGeName" in the URL and accordingly as page name.%0a%0a--[[~Henning]] October 07, 2008, at 01:29 PM%0a%0aA: It appears that PmWiki does not require prepratory configuration for special characters, but the Server (Windows/IIS) has to be enabled to employ (for example) German umlaut characters.%0a%0aUnfortuately, my service provider (while solving the problem) did not tell me exactly what settings of the server had to be changed to fix the problem, but after he made some changes to the server, PmWiki worked just fine with special characters. --[[~Henning]] October 13, 2008, at 06:56 AM%0a%0a----%0a%0aQ: Is it possible to change the standard - setting "text color" from black to green ?%0aThank you !!%0a-> Norbert Hirsch%0a-%3c 081004%0a%0aA: The easiest way to change the text color for your entire wiki is to change the "color" setting in your skins' .css file. For instance I have changed mine to:\\%0a[@ color: #1a1a1a; @]\\%0a[[~Ian MacGregor]]%0a%0a'''Thank you very much Ian MacGregor'''\\%0aI thought too, that's the normal way, but I only try "font-color:" and "text-color:"\\%0aNow it works.%0a-> Norbert Hirsch%0a-%3c 081006%0a----%0a%0aQ: I cannot change Title of my page even by following all the guidelines.%0a-> Kindly see this http://www.shubhkriti.net/shubhkritiwiki/pmwiki.php %25red%25 ''this link does not work''%0aThank You%0a-> Shubhkriti domains[at]shubhkriti.co.in%0a-%3c September 25, 2008%0a%0aA: See [[PmWiki/Page Directives]]%0a----%0a%0aQ: How do I get comments into my code?%0aThank you%0a-> amir%0a-%3c September 14, 2008%0a%0aA: The various types of comments are discussed [[PmWiki/CommentMarkup | here]].%0a[[~Ian MacGregor]]%0a%0a----%0aQ: Is there a way that you can identify who made which edits on the wiki page?%0a-> For example, if Bob adds a comment or makes a change to information on a wiki page is there a way that you can have the author name, "Bob", show up next to the changes they made?  This seems like a really simple and useful idea, and its what I expected when I think of a collaborative wiki, however I can't find ANY information about this type of function?  Can anyone help me?%0aThank you,%0a-> Carl%0a-%3c September 8, 2008%0a%0a-%3c September 9, 2008%0aA: You can require people to put something into the Author box when editing by adding $EnablePostAuthorRequired=1; to the config.php file. Then whatever they put will appear next to Recent Changes. I'm guessing that if you require people to log in then you'd have more control over what was in the Author box as well.%0aHope that helps,%0a-> '''Liz'''%0a----%0a%0aQ: Page text variables and tables?%0a-> I'm trying to have variables in a table (advanced) that are used from other pages, but the variables doesn't seem to be recognized when embedded in a table (following a [=(:cell:)=]).%0a-> I'm running the latest version, 2.2.0-beta65, and the variables are working correctly when not in a table.%0aIs there a way to get this working or am I perhaps trying the wrong thing?, are there any other way to do this?%0aThank you,%0a-> david%0a-%3c 080527%0a%0a-%3c 080529%0aA: To answer myself I have gotten it to (partly) work.%0aThere are two different markups that works from within a table.%0a%0a1. '''[=(:variable01:value:)=]'''%0aIf you place this within a table cell the value does not show in the table but at the place that are calling the variable. As expected.%0a%0a2. '''[=(:variable01 :value:)=]''' with a space after the variable render the value as "[=(:variable01 :value:)=]" in the table cell and as "value" in the place calling the variable.%0a%0aI haven't found a way to render the above as "value" in the source table cell.%0a-> ''-david''%0aA: Can you please issustrate this issue by creating a [[test/]] page?%0a%0a----%0aQ: Disabling buttons like "View", "Edit, "History" etc.%0a%0aI would like to disable the buttons at the top of my pmwiki page, but i don't know where to do. I hope someone could help me!%0aAlso i would like to disable the "text" on the top of my wiki, there's always posted the name of my wiki and the directory the user actually is.%0aThanks a lot!%0a-%3c Apr 8, 2008%0a%0aA: This is possible by changing the [[PmWiki/SkinTemplates]]. (Note that by merely editing out the buttons, the actions they command will still be available for users who know how to operate PmWiki by typing the request URL manually.) --[[~Henning]] April 10, 2008, at 06:59 AM%0a%0aA: You could also use the [[PmWiki/page directive(s)]] [@(:noaction:)@]%0a----%0a%0aQ: Using pmwiki with WebAuth%0a-> I'm trying to use pmwiki with access restricted by WebAuth at my university (Stanford).  When restricting access with WebAuth (https://webauth.duke.edu/), I am able to view the wiki, but am not able to make edits to pages--kind of defeating the purpose of the wiki!  I think it's a sessions-related problem, but am not sure.%0a%0aHas anyone figured out a work around, or solution to this problem?%0a%0aI wasn't able to find anything discussing this problem on the FAQ, or elsewhere online.  I know pmwiki has a password protection feature, but I want to both keep the wiki secure while not forcing my users to remember yet another password.%0a%0aThanks!%0a-%3c Apr 4, 2008%0a----%0a%0aQ: Core.%3cnumber> files in my PmWiki root?%0a-> I just looked in the PmWiki folder on my site (I've been using PmWiki for a few months, but I only have about 50 articles in it) and I found these files that I never noticed before:%0a* core.15468 (size 14 004 224 bytes)%0a* core.15615 (size 0 bytes)%0a* core.16138 (size 0 bytes)%0a* core.16211 (size 0 bytes)%0a%0aWhat's up with these (especially the 14-meg one)? Are they essential to the functionality of PmWiki or just some error-dumps I can safely delete?%0a%0aMerçi.%0a-%3c Mar 22, 2008%0a%0a%25Py%25 These are not PmWiki files. They are possibly traces of programs that crashed at some point. You can most likely safely delete them. --[[~Petko]] February 01, 2009, at 11:39 AM%0a%0a----%0a%0aQ: XML export/import filters?%0a-> I've been asked to translate documentation that is kept in about 200 Pmwiki pages. The translation has to be performed in a translation memory system (TMS - basically, a specialized database system, if you've never heard of it).%0a%0aIdeally, this means getting the database to import the Pmwiki page source, extract the visible text from all the formatting, let us translate it, and then export Pmwiki page source again with all the formatting intact but the translations inserted in place of the original text.%0a%0aThe main problem here is that no TMS (to my knowledge) understands Pmwiki syntax, and the project does not justify programming a custom filter for this purpose. A feasible workaround would be to export the page source from Pmwiki as XML and write a filter for that TMS' usually have pretty good XML support which would only need to be configured right.%0a%0aTherefore my question: Do XML filters for Pmwiki exist that preserve all the formatting? Or are there other filters that may be useful (e.g., Word), i.e., that export all formatting so that it can be imported again with the translation? Or are there even more direct TMS interfaces?%0a%0aSearching on this site and the wide interwebs has failed to turn up anything, so any hints would be welcome.%0a%0aThanks%0aJan%0a-%3c Mar 16, 2008%0a%0a----%0a%0aQ: I can't get my pmwiki site to ask me for a password.%0a-> I put: '''@@$DefaultPasswords['edit'] = crypt('edit_password'); @@'''in local/config.php and i can edit every page of my site from any computer without using a password.  I know local/config.php is working because I changed my title:'''%0a'''$WikiTitle = 'example';'''%0a-> I would like to set a password so that only people who know my password can edit my site.  I also tried setting passwords in the attributes page and it seemed to have no effect%0a-%3c Feb 14, 2008%0a%0aA: Your situation has too many possible explanations for this to be an adequate venue for solving it.  You need to address your Q to the [[mailing list(s)]].  I'm sure someone(s) there will be able to help you.  Do include what version of the software you're using, and whether you've added any other recipes (add-ins).  Best of luck!%0a%0aA: See also [[PmWiki/passwords]] and [[PmWiki/Passwords admin]]%0a%0aA: Ensure there is no "#" before the $%0a%0a----%0a%0aQ: single quotes don't seem to work for me%0a-> every time I try to use quotes to bold, italic etc, it saves multiple quotes and it doesn't change the formatting  it just keeps inserting quotes over and over again...%0a%0aA: Please reproduce on a [[test/]] page, or provide a link to your ''non working'' example.%0a%0a%0a----%0a%0aQ: I'd like to track how often are files with certain extensions (pdf,zip,...) downloaded in PmWiki.%0a-> On another site I maintain, I use a TCL script to postprocess HTML and insert%0a%0a[=%3ca href="file.pdf" onClick="javascript:urchinTracker ('/downloads/file.pdf');"> pdf %3c/a>=]%0a%0acalls to urchinTracker. Is there any way to do something similar in PmWiki?%0a%0aThanks.%0a-%3c Jan 27, 2008%0a%0a%25Py%25 See [[http://article.gmane.org/gmane.comp.web.wiki.pmwiki.user/48638 | Tracking downloads in PmWiki ]] (recipe in the mailing list). --[[~Petko]] February 01, 2009, at 11:39 AM%0a----%0aQ: Is there anyway to use Javascript, PHP, or some other language in a .tmpl file?%0a-> I'm trying to hide the sidebar when a page is being edited (?action=edit is at the end of the url). I wrote some code to do this in javascript, but I think its disabled. Is there anyway do this with some kind of code?%0a%0aA: Your could use the [@(:noleft:)@] [[PmWiki/page directive(s)]] with [[PmWiki/conditional markup]], (see [[Test/EditNoLeft]]), but this doesn't work quite as you would expect.%0a%0aA: Instead add the [@(:noleft:)@] [[PmWiki/page directive(s)]] to the [[Site.Edit Form]].%0a%0a----%0aQ: Is it correct that there is a [[Site.PageNotFound]], but no Group/PageNotFound? --[[~Henning]] November 30, 2007, at 11:22 AM%0a%0aA: That is correct. Site/PageNotFound takes care of any instance in which a page is not found anywhere in the wiki, so there isn't really a need for a Group/PageNotFound since that would be taken care of by Site/PageNotFound for any group. --[[~Ian MacGregor]]%0a%0a----%0aQ: How can I define what PageNotFound page to use?%0a-> My wiki does not use my Site/PageNotFound page, but instead displays "Describe FooBar here.", and I have no idea where it gets that message from or how I could change it. $SiteGroup is set (implicitely) to '''Site''', and I have no idea how I could have screwed up the configuration of my wiki so that Site/PageNotFound is not respected. (I'm using 2.1.27) --[[~Henning]] November 30, 2007, at 11:22 AM%0a%0aA: Your problem is caused by the [[Cookbook/MarkupExtensions]] recipe which defines the default text for a page that is not found. Comment out the line ...%0a%0a[@$DefaultPageTextFmt = 'Describe [[$Group/$Title]] here.';@]%0a%0ain extendmarkup.php to restore normal Site/PageNotFound behaviour. --[[~Henning]] November 30, 2007, at 12:07 PM%0a%0a----%0aQ: Is it possible to run PmWiki on a server that does not run on port 80, but on port 8080 for example? I could not find any configuration setting for the port number.%0a%0aA: Simply set $ScriptUrl to a url that includes the port number.  For example:%0a%0a->[@$ScriptUrl = 'http://example.com:8080/pmwiki/pmwiki.php';@]%0a%0a--[[~Pm]]%0a%0aThanks a lot! Great piece of software. Your support is even better than a lot of commercial companies are going to achieve ;-)%0a%0a-- Markus%0a%0a----%0a%0aQ: I added some users and passwords via AuthUser.%0a-> I also added ++include_once("$FarmD/scripts/authuser.php"); $Author = $AuthId;++ in two rows to my config.php.%0a-> Although I am able to login, my name is not preset in the author field, and in All Recent Changes there is a question mark. I can type in a name in the author field, then this one is shown in All Recent Changes. But I want to have just the login name.%0a->I know that this is possible and works fine because I have another wiki and everything is fine. The new wiki uses the files from the "old" wiki, I just copied them to another folder. So I really don't know why they don't work and I can't find the mistake! Can someone help me? [[~Marvin]] November 12, 2007, at 09:45 AM%0a%0aA: Ok, I think the problem is, that the $FarmD veriable uses the wrong wiki, because recently I was logged in with a username I use in one of my other wikis, although this name doesn't exist in the new wiki. So my question now: How can I tell my wiki, what URL for $FarmD to use? Here it says, that the wiki finds $FarmD by itself.. but it's the wrong one! I want the new wiki to be independent! [[~Marvin]] November 15, 2007, at 06:10 AM%0a%0aA: $FarmD isn't a url -- it's a filesystem path that indicates where the PmWiki software is loaded.  The problem you're describing sounds like it has more to do with cookies than anything else.  Try removing the [@$Author = $AuthId;@] line from your config -- PmWiki automatically sets the author name from a login name if present.  --[[~Pm]]%0a%0aQ: It doesn't work :( I log in with the username and password, and in allrecentchanges it shows a "?" instead of my username. [[~Marvin]] November 25, 2007, at 08:23 AM%0a%0a----%0aQ:How can I get PmWiki to support links that include special characters, such as in Notepad++ ?%0aAt the moment the ++ just gets stripped.%0a%0aA: Maybe using [[PmWiki/special Characters]] will give you a work-around.%0a%0a----%0a%0aQ:How do I remove a space from the value of a variable? It's not a page name.... need a trimleft (trimspace?) type function.%0a-> I have a lot of personnel records that have their names embedded {FirstnameLastname(dollarsign):Blah1} and a form where a name is entered "Firstname Lastname" into say {thisPerson}. So I would like to be able to do something like {{thisPerson}$:Blah1} and have it point to whichever variable I was looking for at the time. When I try it now I end up close but no cigar... just need to lose the space and I'm there. Any help?%0a%0aThanks!%0amk%0a-%3c 16 Oct 2007%0a%0aNon-answer:  This is getting into fairly advanced material.  You really would do well to refer it to the [[mailing lists]]!%0a%0aNon-Answer-Ack: Thanks!%0a----%0aQ:Hey, I managed to install, and its running pmwiki off my root with a index wrapper, but when i click on InitialSetupTasks it just returns with "No input file specified" - what did i do wrong!? Thanks, Chris%0a%0a%0a----%0aQ:A bit juvenile to ask but can I directly show html code through the cms.%0ae.g. I have like a 10 page (i.e. 10 html files) document connected together with an index.htm , can I directly show it one of the frames? Secondly, Is there any applect which can go through a complete folder and sub folder to generate a page with links to these index files (each connecting to a different document and thus sub folders)?%0a%0aA: I believe the recipe [[Cookbook/IncludeUrl]] might be useful to display html directly. --[[~Henning]] October 05, 2007, at 06:50 AM%0a----%0aQ: How do you link to a category without the referring page being entered into the category?  I have a People category. When I link to it from the Homepage, it lists Homepage under People.%0a%0aA: In your example, since you probably don't want to see any HomePage (from any group), you could simply exclude pages with the name HomePage in the pagelist that you use in the header or footer of your Category group, like this:  [@(:pagelist link=Category.{*$Name} name-HomePage list=normal:)@]%0a%0aA: You can't. PmWiki unfortunately does not distinguish between tagging a page with a category, eg [@[[!Wysiwyg]]@] and referring to a category, eg [@Category/Wysiwyg@]. See also [[Category.Category]], and vote for PITS:00447.%0a%0aA: Have a look at [[http://article.gmane.org/gmane.comp.web.wiki.pmwiki.user/42515/]] to get a working solution using intermap links. [[~gb]] November 11, 2009, at 12:24 PM%0a%0a----%0aQ: I am unable to upload files with the upload password enabled.%0a-> If I attach the file as usual while editing, save the page, click the link to add the file, enter my password, browse to the file, press the upload button, enter password again, enter password a third time, then I receive the error no file uploaded and I am back at the browse for file screen. I can upload files fine when the upload password is disabled. The edit and read page passwords seem to work no problem just not the upload password. Admin password does not work either for upload. I am running wiki on a stick cookbook recipe with the abyss webserver.%0a%0aA: I had this exact same problem, for me the problem was with my browser rejecting cookies so that the password didn't get saved correctly (appears to be a bug with Safari 6.0).  Check to make sure your cookie setup is correct and that you don't have an adblocker blocking cookies.  To test that it's nothing to do with your php setup or permissions set your password to nothing and try again (eg. in config.php set @@$DefaultPasswords['upload'] = "";@@), for me I could suddenly upload images.  Then I tried with a different browser and it worked fine.  YMMV.  -- [[~AdamShand]]%0a----%0a%0aQ: How do I limit the page width or word wrap independently of spaces?%0a-> I have a very long piece of text with very few spaces.  I want to show the text on the page without having it increase the page width.  I also want the user to be able to copy the text as is, which is the reason I don't want to use the forced linebreaks.  When they copy the text, I need it still to be copied as a single line.%0a%0aI've tried putting the text into a cell in a table and setting the width to 100%25 but this seems to have no effect.  Is it possible to enforce word wrapping at 100%25 of the window, without regards for space characters?%0a%0a----%0a%0aQ: How can someone insert Project Wonderful ads into their wiki?%0a-> I've seen them used here before, but I can't find any information on how they can be added.%0a%0a----%0a%0aQ: I'm trying to configure some custom markup.%0a-> It's basically a markup word and a path+filename. Example @@(:testmarkup /pmwiki/pub/picture.jpg:)@@. This will have to be translated to [@%3ca href='/pmwiki/pub/picture.jpg'>Image%3c/a>@]%0aHow would this look like?%0a%0aQ: Related question: How could I add a 2nd argument?%0a-> Example: @@(:testmarkup /pmwiki/pub/picture.jpg This is the picture description:)@@ that translates to [@%3ca href='/pmwiki/pub/picture.jpg'>This is the picture description%3c/a>@]%0aHow would this look like?%0a%0aAugust 14th 2007%0a%0a----%0aQ: Why when I save a page and the browser timesout?%0a-> We have been working with no problems for a few weeks now with version 2.2.0-beta55 without a problem. Today, on certain pages, when we edit them and try and save them the browser timesout (PHP timesout on the server). I cannot edit the page from then on. I manually delete the page from the command line, create a new page through pmwiki, paste the old text into the new page and save it. But it hangs again. I upgraded to beta63 with no change. Can we rebuild an index file somewhere to fix the problem?%0a%0aA: We ran into a similar problem. Our problem was that a page was being included by itself (recursive). A footer was including itself. Once we eliminated that, the timeouts went away.%0a%0a----%0aQ: "action=edit" and Searching doesn't respond anymore.%0a-> I used pmwiki since about 1 year without any trouble, but since 6.8.07 whenever I try to edit a page, the browser starts "loading" but absolutely nothing happens. It's the same, when i try to search something using the search-field - no response, and a timeout after waiting a while.%0aI updated to the newest beta-release but this changed nothing. How can i solve this?%0a%0a%0a----%0a%0aQ: How do I enable searching?%0aWhenever I use the search box, site/search or ?action=search&q=... I do not see any results. Do I have to enable search, or make an index, or something? I have a pageindex file, it has some stuff in it.%0a%0aA: Have you got a URL we can look at? Does the [[Search]] documentation provide you with any assistance?%0a%0aNo, sorry, no URL, its for a private intranet site... The documentation doesn't provide any help, but i did get the search results to display, kind of.%0a%0aIt now just displays:%0a-> [@%0aResults of search for  /:%0a0 pages found out of 0 pages searched.%0a@]%0a%0aDoes PmWiki need a special index file? what should I do?%0a%0aAnother possibility:%0a%0aI had a similar problem with a locally hosted copy of PmWiki.  Eventually I tracked it down to line 154 of scripts/pagelist.php.  If I removed "@$_REQUEST" from array_merge function call, my search worked fine.  Because the $_REQUEST array includes all cookies for the server, including cookies for unrelated projects, I think some cookies for other testing sites were conflicting with PmWiki's search.  I removed some unneeded cookies, restored pagelist.php to its original form, and search has worked fine.%0a%0aTo recap:%0a#Remove @$_REQUEST from line 154 of scripts/pagelist.php.%0a-OR-%0a#Delete any cookies you don't need for that server.%0a%0a----%0a%0aQ: Can I preempt the edit password prompt on links that don't yet have pages?%0a-> The nature of my wiki requires edit passwords. When I started my wiki, I encouraged editors to insert what I call "pre-links" in articles. For example, an editor creating an article about "Bob" will go ahead and link references to "Mary" or "Joe" even if no articles exist on Mary or Joe. My reasoning was that other editors would notice these links and future articles would be encouraged as a result. This is very confusing to a common non-editor/reader, though, whose only interest is browsing the site. They click one of the links with the ? mark beside it, and can't understand why they're getting a prompt for a password. I would like to insert a message, "This article has not been written yet. Please check back later" and also have a way for editors to click from THAT page, submit their password, and proceed to create the new page. For the moment, I've asked editors to stop inserting pre-links until this can be sorted out.%0a%0aA: The page that is displayed when you are prompted for a password is [[Site.AuthForm]]. You could take the contents of the AuthForm page and place them in a new page, are change the AuthForm page to have the message you require, and a link to the new page (and a link to where you came from).%0a%0a----%0aQ: How can I limit the pages users can see?%0a-> When I browse to my pmwiki on (for example) [@http://%3cip>/pmwiki/pub/skins@], people can see the contents of that directory. Should I put empty index.html's in those directories? (any specifics I have to watch out for?)%0a%0aA: Putting index.html in these directories is a good solution. The approach PmWiki uses is to add a .htaccess file to its directories. You can copy this into all the directories you wish to restrict the contents to, but additionally you could enable the access to index.html (which could redirect to, say, your homepage).%0a%0aQ: When I browse to [@http://%3cip>/pmwiki/sdofhaewh98awe@] (i.e. garbage) I always get some default page.%0aWhich default page is this and can I change it? If people type a wrong URL I would want them to see nothing. (would this interfere with creating new wiki's from non-existing links?)%0a%0aA: The default page is [[Site.PageNotFound]].%0aWhat do you mean by nothing - do you mean you don't want to navigate away from the page you are at?%0aAfter you are making a request, something has to be displayed?%0a%0aIdeally I would likie to show a 404-not-found when a user types a URL that doesn't exist. When I delete the Site.PageNotFound file I still get some empty page that contains my sidebar and tabmenu (simpletab skin).%0a%0aThankyou!%0aAugust 6th 2007%0a%0a----%0aQ: I keep on getting a error message when use IE7 to view my website (http://wiki.lovedaywetlands.org) can you guys and gals check it out for me and send me a email via the website.%0a%0aNB:: I have tried the site in Safari Mac & Windows, Firefox Mac & Windows it all works fine on them but not on IE7.%0a%0aHELP%0a%0aCheers%0a%0a----%0a%0aQ: PmWiki seems to be unable to read the '-config.php-' file.%0aShould I change '-permissions-' to '-"/local"-' folder to '-755-'? Should I change all permissions to all folders to '-755-'? Is it safe?%0aNikos%0a%0aChanging '-permissions-' to '-755-' didn't solve the problem. By the way the installation is in a free hosting service and they place ads in the pages (if it is of any importance). Nikos%0a%0aProblem solved: I should have deleted the "'-# -' " before an option. That is '-# $EnableGUIButtons = 1;-' should become '-$EnableGUIButtons = 1;-' . Wish you said so in the beginning of the the '-config.php-' file. Nikos%0a----%0aQ:Source page for Page Text Variables?%0aIf I use in a page many Page Text Variables from same source page, can I somehow set it as default for Page Text Variables?%0a%0aTaavetti%0a----%0aQ: Does this make sense?%0aI added this  rewrite-engine line to block bad urls in .htaccess%0aThe aim is to exclude all requests trying to attack the php-engine with special characters.%0aNow calls like:%0a-> [@%0akolibriethos.de/Ethos/Homepage%25A7%0akolibriethos.de/Ethos/Homepage(§%0akolibriethos.de/Ethos/Home\@age%0abut not%0ahttp://www.kolibriethos.de/Ethos/Homepage?action=browse§%0awill be blocked.%0a%0a# Define the rewrite base.%0aRewriteBase /%0a#Allgemeine Regeln: Schutz vor Sonderzeichen%0aRewriteRule [^a-zäüößA-ZÄÜÖ0-9?:#+.%25_=\/\s]+ not_accepted_go_away.txt [L]%0a@]%0aTo block request content with special characters (like ?action=browse§ ), \\%0aI needed to include a check-function in my protect.php \\%0a(more information under: www.kolibriethos.de/Ethos/Sicherheit )\\%0aMany greetings%0a%0aHans%0a%0a----%0aQ: I am using the [[Cookbook/TraceTrail]] recipe on my wiki.%0a-> It shows the trail in this structure: Category/Pagename. Is there a possibility that it only shows the Pagename, but still links to the right page? Thanks for answers, [[~Marvin]] May 31, 2007, at 02:36 AM%0a%0aA: Have a look at [[WikiTrails-Talk]] : « In the bulletted list of links, use [@[[Group.Page|+]]@] to get the page titles, both in this list and in the trails. » [[~gb]] February 08, 2010, at 11:58 AM%0a----%0a%0aQ: My Search-Field does not work anymore after I created a new Skin.%0a-> I left the form action the same ("action='{$ScriptUrl}'"), though. You can have a look at http://www.dasbrot.info/wiki/ . Everything else works fine, after I got a bit into the system.%0aBest Greetings%0aRoman%0a%0aA: Hallo Roman,\\%0awo genau ist Dein Problem? Das Suchfeld funktioniert bei mir wunderbar, du musst nur neben die Lupe klicken und zwar erstaunlicherweise relativ weit rechts in das weiße rein, ich hab erst auf die Lupe gepatscht, da springt der Cursor nicht rein. Dann einfach auf enter drücken, dann kam ich ganz normal auf die Suchergebnis-Seite und wenn ich z.B. "Vorstand" eingebe kriege ich als Ergebnis "DerVerein".\\%0aLiebe Grüße, [[~Marvin]] June 11, 2007, at 03:07 AM%0a----%0aQ:I tried to  realize the hr line with different colors.%0aIs this the right way?%0a(:markup class=horiz:)%0a%25define=blockline block  border-bottom="dashed 5px #00EE00" border-top="solid 1px #00FF11"%25%0a%25blockline%25 %25blockline%25%0a%25define=blockline block    border-top="solid 5px #FF0000"%25%0a%25blockline%25 %25blockline%25 my pmwiki: http://www.kolibriethos.de   more Examples: http://www.kolibriethos.de/Main/Design%0a(:markupend:)%0a%0aA: It works. Another solution might be to change the formatting of ''hr'' in your local.css'^[[PmWiki/Skins#further|#]]^' file.%0a%0aMany thanks!  (It doesnt work in some older private Wikis. I will try to find out why and which configuration is necessary!)%0a----%0aQ: Our pmwiki sidebar has gotten longer over time and gets cut off at the bottom by pages with little content on them when we use the IE7 browser.%0a-> How do I make the sidebar take precedence over the length of the main page content so that the sidebar does not get cut off at the bottom on IE7?;  Thanks - CR%0a%0aA: If you are using the default template the sidebar is simply a cell in a table. Therefore neither should take precedence. Check to see if some CSS or change to the template has caused this behaviour.%0a----%0aQ: I want a gui button that adds the code "&amp;nbsp;" .%0a-> (Hah - figured it out by writing this question. Sorry.)%0a$GUIButtons['nbsp'] = array(660,'&amp;nbsp;', '', '','$GUIButtonDirUrlFmt/nbs.gif"$[nbsp]"');  Thanks - LFS%0a----%0aQ: I have a link in my SideBar for an FTP location, is there anyway I can carry my login credentials through from the initial Wiki Login to autopopulate the FTP login box so I can just go right through to the FTP site?%0a-> When the box pops up to login to the FTP location, the credentials are the same as the credentials used to login to the Wiki site. Please help! -Brent%0a----%0aQ: How do I get a checkbox on wiki page?%0a-> It is not defined in the special character section. Please help [[tami clark]]%0a%0aHi:  have a look at [[Cookbook:Input]], which describes PmWiki's built-in forms markup.  Also look at [[Cookbook:Cookbook#FormTools]] for other, related information.%0aA: Try also searching for ''box html entity'', and you will find &#9744; &#9746; &#9745; &#10003; &#10004; &#10005; &#10006; &#10007; &#10008;%0a----%0aQ: I've added a comment-button to my wiki which does this: pmwiki/pmwiki.php?n=Comments.Main-HomePage?action=view%0a-> It shows the content of the group "Comment" that is made for the respective page (in the above case for Main-Homepage). Now if I use this comment-button for pages that do not have a comment yet it says something like "Page not found". Of course it does so because there isn't such a page yet. Is there a way if I am on the page "Main-Articles" which hasn't a respective comment-page yet for making such a comment page automatically by clicking on the Comment-Button? Also at the moment the small question mark with the dotted underline for non-existing comment-button's will not show. Thanks a lot. -- [[~Torsten]] April 30, 2007, at 02:45 PM%0a%0a----%0a%0aQ: I figured out why I were having trouble installing. New question: Why all the different file-extensions instead of making them all something like .PmWiki and .Site files?%0a%0aHere's the thing: The browser based file manager I was using couldn't read all of your files because it didn't have the necessary fileextensions added. And who can blame it. You have a load of these weird fileextensions seemingly for no reason. Why is it that you have to have a load of different files like PmWiki.WikiWord, PmWiki.WikiPages and Site.AuthUser? Why couldn't you just make two new filetypes instead of 108!? You could just make .PmWiki and .Site files, making the files mentioned above become WikiWord.PmWiki, WikiPages.Pmwiki and AuthUser.Site.%0aOr maybe they could even be textfiles?.. I guess I'm way too unexperienced in this area to know what I'm talking about, but it just seems like such a weird thing to do seeing as most other wikis do just fine without it, and maaany people out there prefer to make use of browserbased filemanagers. Isn't there some way to work around making hundreds of new fileextensions?%0a[[~Aray]] April 17, 2007, at 23:44%0a%0aThey aren't extensions in the conventional way.  The files are wiki pages, where the filename is each page's name in a GroupName.PageName format.  I don't think there's a way around that. --[[~Hagan(Fox)]]%0a%0a----%0a%0aQ: Hi! Why is e.g. my local folder empty when I view it in the filemanager (www.110mb.com) and all I can see is a .htaccess file in there when I check it out on the comp?%0aI am quite new in everything that has to do with web-developing. I have managed to establish this webpage, and now I wanted to give your wiki a try. I've installed other wikis with success, but this one is giving me some problems. All I can see in the zip is these .htaccess files, where I thought there should be various other files... Anyways, I upload the zip, I unzip the folder, I create the index.php, and the page kinda works. But on pretty much everything except the HomePage link, there are these questionmarks attached for some reason. Every link that's got a questionmark attached has no content. I just can't figure out what's wrong :(%0a%0aWill I get slapped for my extreme lack of knowledge now? :o%0a%0a'''Edit:''' Oh, I realized that those questionmarks might be ''supposed'' to be there, so I'll add this then: Editing doesn't work, it just reloads the page. The same thing happens if I try to access the recent changes, or the search for instance. In short: Nothing works!\\%0a[[~Aray]] April 15, 2007, at 02.10 AM%0a%0aA: The question marks indicate a link to a wiki page that doesn't exist.%0a%0aYou are correct that there should be various files in most of the directories, although the [@local/@] and [@cookbook/@] directories are empty except for a .htaccess file.  Make sure you have installed all of the files in [@scripts/@] and [@wikilib.d/@] .  --[[~Hagan(Fox)]]%0a%0a'''Edit2:''' That's the problem. The wikilib.d folder is just stuffed with files like .authform and .pageactions, and the browserbased filemanager I'm using can't seem to read these. Anywow, if I simply upload the whole zip (pmwiki-2.1.27), unzip it and run the pmwiki.php file, that page with the questionmarks is loaded. If I take a look at my filemanager after doing this,