g a white line%0alike here I have just one paragraph, which is good and the expected behaviour.%0a%0a# But if I do%0athe same%0ain a list%0athe result is quite different.%0a(:markupend:)%0a%0aIs this expected behaviour? If yes, is there any switch that%0aI can use to change it?%0a%0aA:  Yes, this is expected.  Within a list-item, a linebreak is reflected in the output.  A workaround, allowing you to break lines but stay on the same line in the output, is to put a back-slash at the end of the line (being sure there are no spaces following the backslash):%0a%0a(:markup class=horiz:)%0a# If I end \%0awith a backslash, \%0athe output \%0ais all on one line.%0a(:markupend:)%0a%0aThank you for the answer ([[~Romano_Giannetti]]). I had another answer on the list by Patrick, that I copy here, given that it adds information and maybe can promote this item to a FAQ candidate.%0a%0aIf you want all of the text to be part of a single list item, then indent%0athe second and subsequent lines to align with the first character of the%0afirst line.  Thus:%0a%0a(:markup class=horiz:)%0a# But if I do%0a  the same%0a  in a list%0a  the result is quite different.%0a(:markupend:)%0a%0aThis results in a single list item containing "But if I do the same in a list%0athe result is quite different".%0a%0aThis indentation can also be used to put paragraphs within list items, as in:%0a%0a(:markup class=horiz:)%0a# This is%0a  list item%0a  number 1.%0a%0a  This paragraph is part of the above list item.%0a%0a# This is%0a  list item%0a  number 2.%0a%0aThis paragraph terminates the above list.%0a(:markupend:)%0a%0a%0a----%0aQ: (03/16/2007) Getting PmWiki on CD%0a%0aIs there any possibility to copy/export/transfer/whatever PmWiki on CD? I would like to create a guide with the help of PmWiki and give it out to customers on CD so they can run it locally without the hassle of installing something. Is that possible, and if yes, how is it done?%0a%0aA: Try [[Cookbook:Standalone]]. --[[~Henning]] March 16